lation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/2888">The Universal Credit and Miscellaneous Amendments (No.2) Regulations 2014 (S.I. 2014/2888)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e53088a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/2888/regulation/1/1">regs. 1(1)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e53091a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/2888/regulation/3/1/a/i">3(1)(a)(i)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-1c2ec5ad979435c900036cab5c0a9b39" marker="F26"><p>Words in <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e55754a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/2">reg. 2</ref> inserted (6.4.2025) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e55757a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2025/201">The Neonatal Care Leave and Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Regulations 2025 (S.I. 2025/201)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e55760a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2025/201/regulation/1/2">regs. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e55763a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2025/201/regulation/19/2">19(2)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-472e51cbfaf90d64cfe7fa9e638ce846" marker="F27"><p>Words in reg. 2 inserted (6.4.2020) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44913a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354">The Parental Bereavement Leave and Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Regulations 2020 (S.I. 2020/354)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44916a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354/regulation/1">regs. 1</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44919a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354/regulation/28/2">28(2)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-ce256a7f220120821f5c00b2fc9be622" marker="F28"><p>Words in reg. 2 inserted (31.12.2014) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e50848a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255">The Shared Parental Leave and Statutory Shared Parental Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Order 2014 (S.I. 2014/3255)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e50851a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/1/2">arts. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e50854a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/28/2/c">28(2)(c)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-a581d8b6f8c2e5dee7bf8539104db61e" marker="F29"><p>Words in reg. 2 inserted (6.4.2017) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e48823a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/376">The Social Security (Restrictions on Amounts for Children and Qualifying Young Persons) Amendment Regulations 2017 (S.I. 2017/376)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e48826a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/376/regulation/1">regs. 1</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e48829a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/376/regulation/2/2">2(2)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-78763d1ca218bb8679d87d946e994a3e" marker="F30"><p>Words in <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e46995a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/2">reg. 2</ref> substituted (4.4.2022) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e46998a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2022/260">The Universal Credit and Employment and Support Allowance (Terminal Illness) (Amendment) Regulations 2022 (S.I. 2022/260)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47001a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2022/260/regulation/1/2">regs. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47004a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2022/260/regulation/2/2">2(2)</