0" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/1/3">arts. 1(3)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e52700a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/28/3/b">28(3)(b)</ref> (with <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e52703a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/35/1">art. 35(1)</ref>)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-daf99fa9d03f8f18bc8a4bbb985c7010" marker="F153"><p>Words in reg. 32(2)(b) inserted (31.12.2014) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e51412a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255">The Shared Parental Leave and Statutory Shared Parental Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Order 2014 (S.I. 2014/3255)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e51415a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/1/2">arts. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e51418a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/28/3/c">28(3)(c)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-4a65ec5c273dddc91f1723cb7d19e935" marker="F154"><p>Words in reg. 32(2)(b) inserted (6.4.2020) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e45009a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354">The Parental Bereavement Leave and Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Regulations 2020 (S.I. 2020/354)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e45012a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354/regulation/1">regs. 1</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e45015a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354/regulation/28/3">28(3)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-35dd6c126b70f20566916e3dfc34834a" marker="F155"><p>Words in <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e55774a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/32/2/b">reg. 32(2)(b)</ref> inserted (6.4.2025) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e55777a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2025/201">The Neonatal Care Leave and Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Regulations 2025 (S.I. 2025/201)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e55780a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2025/201/regulation/1/2">regs. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e55783a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2025/201/regulation/19/3">19(3)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-239e25c542f83407d91ea057a3fc7a09" marker="F156"><p>Reg. 33(1)(za) inserted (26.11.2014) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e43201a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/2887">The Universal Credit (Digital Service) Amendment Regulations 2014 (S.I. 2014/2887)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e43204a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/2887/regulation/1">regs. 1</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e43207a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/2887/regulation/2/2/a">2(2)(a)</ref> (with <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e43210a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/2887/regulation/5">reg. 5</ref>)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-38443aa4ff9a516430537e8b997a586e" marker="F157"><p>Words in <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44269a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/33/1/za">reg. 33(1)(za)</ref> substituted (16.10.2019) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44272a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2019/1249">The Universal Credit (Childcare Costs and Minimum Income Floor) (Amendment) Regulations 2019 (S.I. 2019/1249)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44275a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2019/1249/regulation/1/3">regs. 1(3)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44278a1