nto force in accordance with art. 1(2)(o) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47857a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/260)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47860a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/1/2/o">arts. 1(2)(o)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47863a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/28/4">28(4)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47866a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/schedule/17">Sch. 17</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-79d2147a27f61bcea5edf63dbc1675e1" marker="C64"><p>Sch. 4 para. 33 sum maintained (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(2)(o) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47049a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/260)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47052a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/1/2/o">arts. 1(2)(o)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47055a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/28/4">28(4)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47058a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/schedule/17">Sch. 17</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-d118d553e693a12ad96dc614111bc729" marker="C65"><p>Sch. 4 para. 35(4) sum maintained (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(2)(o) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e50958a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/260)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e50961a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/1/2/o">arts. 1(2)(o)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e50964a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/28/4">28(4)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e50967a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/schedule/17">Sch. 17</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-05a52b3548d30166cda83b4787c91712" marker="C66"><p>Sch. 4 para. 36(2) sum maintained (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(2)(o) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41862a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/260)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41865a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/1/2/o">arts. 1(2)(o)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41868a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/28/4">28(4)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41871a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/schedule/17">Sch. 17</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-0113f8723c483d1973a787b1280f588c" marker="C67"><p>Sch. 4 para. 36(3) sum maintained (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(2)(o) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41679a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/260)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41682a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/1/2/o">arts. 1(2)(o)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41685a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/28/4">28(4)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41688a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/schedule/17">Sch. 17</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-49aac1d51abf1b7cb25ba8d736bbdda2" marker="C68"><p>Sch. 4 para. 36(4) sum maintained (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(2)(o) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44968a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/260)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44971a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/1/2/o">arts. 1(2)(o)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44974a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/28/4">28(4)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e44977a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/schedule/17">Sch. 17</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="c2190906" marker="C69"><p>Sch. 5 para. 6 excluded (29.4.2013) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41146a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/386">The Universal Credit (Transitional Provisions) Regulations 2013 (S.I. 2013/386)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41149a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/386/regulation/1/2">regs. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e41152a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/386/regulation/29/5">29(5)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-88c81595f873a789b091eaee32c10da4" marker="C70"><p>Sch. 5 Pt. 4 para. 10(2) sum maintained (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(3)(p) of the amending S.I.) (where reg. 20 of <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47637a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/725">S.I. 2017/725</ref> applies) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47640a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2022/292">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2022 (S.I. 2022/292)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e47643a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2022/292/article/33/4/a">art. 33(4)(a)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-ed320b43feab4eb1100169ba697baa90" marker="C71"><p>Sch. 5 Pt. 4 para. 11(2) sum maintained (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(3)(p) of the amending S.I.) (where reg. 20 of <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e52229a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/725">S.I. 2017/725</ref> applies) by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e52232a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2022/292">The Social Security Benefits Up   Rating Order 2022 (S.I. 2022/292)</ref>, <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e52235a1310" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2022/292/article/33/4/b">art. 33(4)(b)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165889" marker="M1"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39013a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2012/5">2012 c.5</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165890" marker="M2"><p>See section 173(5) of the Social Security Administration Act 1992. The requirement to refer regulations to the Social Security Advisory Committee does not apply where regulations are contained in a statutory instrument made before the end of the period of six months beginning with the coming into force of the enactment under which the regulations were made.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165892" marker="M3"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39047a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1983/686">S.I. 1983/686</ref>. Article 14 was substituted, and articles 15 and 16 were amended, by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39050a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2001/1420">S.I. 2001/1420</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165894" marker="M4"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39076a1310" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/section/70">Section 70</ref> has been amended by <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39079a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1994/2556">S.I. 1994/2556</ref> and <ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39082a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/1457">S.I. 2002/1457</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165895" marker="M5"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39093a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1992/4">1992 c.4</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165897" marker="M6"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39115a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2007/5">2007 c.5</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165898" marker="M7"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39126a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/379">S.I.2013/379</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165901" marker="M8"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39162a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ssi/2009/210">S.S.I. 2009/210</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165902" marker="M9"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39173a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1999/8">1999 c.8</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165903" marker="M10"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39184a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2003/1">2003 c.1</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165904" marker="M11"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39195a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1995/18">1995 c.18</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165905" marker="M12"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39206a1310" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1994/39">1994 c.39</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c2165906" marker="M13"><p><ref eId="rnb8sic5-d3e39218a1310" href="http://www.legi